column5: the eclipse is starting  If you're on a lake trout lake, the whitefish are spawning in the first rapid above the lake under the blood moon  hopefully somebody is out fishing pics now and can tell us how the bite was
cant see anything here
Raining. What else is new.
Looks good here it's about 1/4 covered but my cell camera will not pick up the dark side. Good luck to everyone fishing today
I'm in Burlington,looking good!
Totally covered now from the top of the ambassador bridge.
I just caught a look at it. The clouds finally moved out. Just a sliver left. Very cool.
Had a great view in Woody. Watched the whole thing.
Got to see it real  well but my iPhone did not do well taking a picture of it.
Clouds cloud and more clouds.
Bill  When the clouds cleared, it was right out your front door. I surprised you didn't get pics.  YA my cell couldn't pic it up either. To many lights around.
I guess I went to bed too early
Thats so romantic....the whitefish out "spawning" in the moonlight
out "spawning" in the moonlight  Those days ( nights) are over..
Cloudy and rain here could not see anything.
I had the camera in the truck going to work this morning every time I'd pull over off the 401 clouds would come in pulled over 4 times then had to say Forkit gonna be late
we managed to catch a few glimpses of it as it started. A shame we don't have a more powerful lens as for about 10 minutes we had a beauty clear view.  Then it slipped behind the trees
Pretty good shots for what your view was!!
The last shot is what I got to see. Nice going.
Thanks for posting the pic Spincast.  Neat to see.
